        "id": "eci_6",
        "name": "Male Contraception Requirements",
        "text": "A male subject must agree to use and to have their female partners of childbearing potential to use a highly effective contraception (i.e., methods with a failure rate of less than 1% per year) as detailed in Appendix VIII of this protocol from the first dose of study treatment, during the treatment period and for at least 3 months after the last dose of study treatment and refrain from donating sperm during this period. Male subjects should always use a barrier method such as condom concomitantly.",
